The Rwandan government has placed capital city Kigali back under total lockdown for 10 days effective July 17, 2021 as the country battles a severe third wave that has seen fatalities increase over the last two weeks. The eight districts placed under lockdown alongside Kigali are - Burera, Gicumbi, Kamonyi, Musanze, Nyagatare, Rubavu, Rwamagana and Rutsiro. The current surge in infections has mainly affected Kigali which represents over half of the country's reported cases, according to Rwanda Biomedical Center's statistics. As at July 16 2021, Rwanda recorded 51,625 Covid-19 cases with 36,478 recoveries and 616 fatalities.